<br>
Once you're on the rampage list, your name is on the list until the mob is dead. You can't clear the rampage list by dying, camping, FD, memblur etc. If you once do something that aggros the mob, you are on its rampage until it's dead. <br>
<br>
The rampage list is not changed by your place on the hate list. If you cast a minor heal in aggro range of the mob before the fight starts you're on the list. If you did that before anyone else aggroed the mob you are FIRST on the list. If you do nothing else at all, and walk into melee range of the mob when it's at 5% and dying, you will be first on the rampage list. <br>
<br>
If you res someone high on the rampage list that died in melee range, you most likely have killed them again. Death does not remove you from the list, nor change your place on the list. <br>
<br>
<br>
Tactics for controling the rampage list. <br>
<br>
1) Every tank class should get on the Rampage list first, with the MT being the last of the tanks to get listed. You don't want your MT taking random damage spikes from rampage..it's like ghetto flurry on the MT. <br>
1a) Rooted mobs- You want to use non-magic arrows/throwing weapons to get on the list or a non-damage spell. If you do enough damage to the mob while setting rampage, you'll get it summoning which is a &quot;bad thing&quot; before the CH chain is started. <br>
2) Every other melee should then get on the rampage list. <br>
<br>
This will ensure that your clerics and wizards can move into melee range if needed with no risk of taking a rampage. The 20 or so melee that are on the list prior will provide a margin of safety. This still won't protect you from normal mob aggro from excessive nuking/healing, but you'll be summoned anyhow. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=roenae>Roenae</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 136<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/5/02 1:39:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2589.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Rampage</span><hr size=1> Nice post, ive wondered about this myself.<br>
